# {{ projectName }}

DARE-shaped MCP server in Python 3.11+ using the FastMCP API.
Default transport: **{{ defaultTransport }}**.

## Setup

```bash
cp .env.example .env
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate    # or .venv\Scripts\activate on Windows
pip install -e ".[dev]"
python -m src.cli            # uses {{ defaultTransport }} transport by default
```

## Test with MCP Inspector

```bash
npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector python -m src.cli
```

## Tools

- `echo` — returns its input. Canonical smoke test.

## Prompts

- `summarize` — placeholder prompt template that takes a `text` argument.

## Transports

Pick at runtime via `--transport stdio|sse|http` or `MCP_TRANSPORT` env:

| Transport | When to use |
|---|---|
| `stdio` (default) | Local CLI agents |
| `sse`             | Web clients via Server-Sent Events |
| `http`            | Streamable HTTP — newest MCP transport |

## Commands

- `python -m src.cli` — start server
- `pytest` — run tests
- `ruff check .` — lint
- `pip-audit` — dependency audit

